subject: p10867202
History: -year-old female with pulmonary fibrosis and CHF with worsening shortness of breath.
Findings: AP and lateral views of the chest. Low lung volumes are seen compatible with patients history of fibrosis. Diffusely increased interstitial markings are seen throughout the lungs, but these appear overall slightly worse when compared to prior. Cardiomediastinal silhouette is grossly unchanged. No acute osseous abnormality is detected.
Impression: Findings compatible with pulmonary fibrosis with likely superimposed edema. Please note that infection cannot be excluded and clinical correlation is necessary.
